<paragraph id="IAS07_12" base="SL29739"><paranum>12</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 7"/><data name="paranum" value="12"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS07_P0035">A single transaction may include <xref base="SL131365" href="IAS07_6.dita#IAS07_6/IAS07_P0018">cash flows<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0030"/></ph></xref> that are classified differently. For example, when the cash repayment of a loan includes both interest and capital, the interest element may be classified as an <xref base="SL131366" href="IAS07_6.dita#IAS07_6/IAS07_P0021">operating activity<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0268"/></ph></xref> and the capital element is classified as a <xref base="SL131368" href="IAS07_6.dita#IAS07_6/IAS07_P0027">financing activity<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0130"/></ph></xref>.</p></body></paragraph>